			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="2438">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>K. E. Ellingson&rsquo;s essay about attempted suicide [&ldquo;<a href="/article/2093">Before and After</a>,&rdquo; April 1999] is what <strong>The Sun</strong> is all about: absolutely the best writing around. By expressing her struggles with living, Ellingson gives voice to the rest of us out here who, at times, wonder if survival is overrated. Reading stories by such gifted writers, I feel that I&rsquo;m not alone, that others find life rather odd at times. <strong>The Sun</strong> is a lifeline.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Jeanie Mortenson<br>La Jolla, California</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

